### Steps to reproduce

**Steps to Reproduce:**
1 - Use the code provided below to create a GridView with items whose visibility can be controlled.
2 - Set the visible property of one of these items to false.
3 - Note that the space occupied by this item is still maintained in the rendering, resulting in unwanted white space.

```
class MainApp extends StatefulWidget {
  MainApp({super.key});

  @override
  State<MainApp> createState() => _MainAppState();
}

class _MainAppState extends State<MainApp> {
  bool box1 = false;
  bool box2 = false;

  @override
  void initState() {
    super.initState();
    setValueBox();
  }

  void setValueBox() {
    Future.delayed(const Duration(seconds: 3), () {
      setState(() {
        box1 = false;
        box2 = true;
      });
    });
  }

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      debugShowCheckedModeBanner: false,
      home: Scaffold(
        appBar: AppBar(),
        body: Padding(
          padding: const EdgeInsets.only(top: 20.0),
          child: GridView(
            shrinkWrap: true,
            gridDelegate: const SliverGridDelegateWithFixedCrossAxisCount(crossAxisCount: 2),
            children: [
              Visibility(
                visible: box1,
                child: Container(
                  height: 100,
                  width: 100,
                  color: Colors.purple,
                  child: const Center(
                    child: Text(
                      'BOX 2',
                      style:...

Team response: I think this is caused by your fixed `crossAxisCount` is always set to 2. You should manage to handle it as a dynamic value for your desire, something like this:

```dart
gridDelegate: SliverGridDelegateWithFixedCrossAxisCount(crossAxisCount: box1 ? 2 : 1),
```

Let me know if it works for your case.

